To install Apache HTTP Server on an Ubuntu system, you can use the apt package manager. Here are the steps:

Update the package index:
- sudo apt update

Install Apache:
- sudo apt install apache2

Verify the installation
- apache2 -v
This command will display the installed version of Apache.

Start the Apache service:
- sudo systemctl start apache2

Enable Apache to start on boot:
- sudo systemctl enable apache2

Check the status of Apache to ensure it is running:
- sudo systemctl status apache2

Open your web browser and visit http://Public-IP-of-the-ubuntu-machine/:

If Apache is installed and running correctly, you should see the default Apache welcome page.
